SUMMARY:

 On December 22, 1993, the International Union, United Automobile, Aerospace and Agricultural Implement Workers
of America-UAW (UAW) petitioned EPA under section 21 of the Toxic Substances Control Act (TSCA), 15 U.S.C. 2620, to
issue test rules under section 4 of TSCA to develop data to aid in the determination of whether machining fluids pose
an unreasonable risk to public health or the environment. This Notice announces EPA's response to UAW's petition.





