upon approval of the final full agenda. CDC reserves the right to terminate co-sponsorship if it does not concur with
the final agenda. 
Because CDC's mission and programs relate to the promotion of health and the prevention of disease, disability, and
premature death, only conferences focusing on such programmatic areas will be considered. Those topics concerned
with health-care and health-service issues and areas other than prevention should be directed to other public health
